'''艾莉莎·懷特格拉茲'''（Alissa White-Gluz）是名加拿大籍的歌手。她是加拿大金屬核樂團[[痛苦處女|痛苦處女]]（The Agonist）的創始者，<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.centurymedia.com/artist.aspx?IdArtist=180 |title=Century Media Records Artist Profile}}</ref>
也是瑞典旋律死亡金屬樂團[[邪神大敵|邪神大敵]]的新主唱。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/arch-enemy-parts-ways-with-singer-angela-gossow-recruits-the-agonists-alissa-white-gluz/ |title=ARCH ENEMY Parts Ways With Singer ANGELA GOSSOW, Recruits THE AGONIST's ALISSA WHITE-GLUZ |publisher=Blabbermouth |date=March 17, 2014}}</ref>

==職涯==
=== 痛苦處女 ===
2004年，19歲的懷特格拉茲和同伴丹尼·馬里諾、克里斯·凱爾斯在蒙特婁創立了樂團[[痛苦處女|痛苦處女]]。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://lithiummagazine.com/interview-alissa-white-gluz-agonist-august-14th-2011 |title=Interview with Alissa White-Gluz of The Agonist |publisher=Lithium Magazine |date=August 14, 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140224132814/http://lithiummagazine.com/interview-alissa-white-gluz-agonist-august-14th-2011 |archivedate=February 24, 2014 }}</ref><br />懷特格拉茲一直擔任該樂團的創作主力，也負責樂團的視覺設計和行銷<ref name="#1">{{cite web |url=https://www.facebook.com/AlissaWhiteGluzFans/info|title=Alissa的自傳}}</ref>，直到她在2014年3月17日<ref>{{cite web |url=http://loudwire.com/angela-gossow-leaves-arch-enemy-agonist-alissa-white-gluz-new-vocalist/|title=Angela Gossow Leaves Arch Enemy, The Agonist’s Alissa White-Gluz Announced as New Vocalist}}</ref>離開痛苦處女。

事後，懷特格拉茲宣稱離開痛苦處女並非她本意。
<ref>{{cite web |url=http://loudwire.com/new-arch-enemy-vocalist-alissa-white-gluz-every-intension-continuing-the-agonist/|title=New Arch Enemy Vocalist Alissa White-Gluz Had Every Intention of Continuing With the Agonist}}</ref>

=== 邪神大敵 ===
2014年3月17日，[[邪神大敵|邪神大敵]]透過媒體宣佈懷特格拉茲取代了[[安琪拉·高索|安琪拉·高索]]，成為樂團的新主唱。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.metalhammer.co.uk/news/angela-gossow-leaves-arch-enemy-new-singer-announced |title=Angela Gossow Leaves Arch Enemy, New Singer Announced |publisher=Metal Hammer |date=March 17, 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140317224704/http://www.metalhammer.co.uk/news/angela-gossow-leaves-arch-enemy-new-singer-announced/ |archivedate=March 17, 2014 }}</ref>

